{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JhSfLkKWVfXFVHnLhT3hZp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package generic\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"bytes\"\n     6→\t\"context\"\n     7→\t\"os\"\n     8→\t\"os/exec\"\n     9→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    10→\n    11→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    12→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/protocol\"\n    13→)\n    14→\n    15→type Adapter struct {\n    16→\tStatusWriter *protocol.StatusWriter // optional: streams live output lines\n    17→\tRunID        string                 // optional: passed as CLOCHE_RUN_ID to child processes\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→func New() *Adapter {\n    21→\treturn &Adapter{}\n    22→}\n    23→\n    24→func (a *Adapter) Name() string {\n    25→\treturn \"generic\"\n    26→}\n    27→\n    28→func (a *Adapter) Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (string, error) {\n    29→\tcmdStr := step.Config[\"run\"]\n    30→\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \"sh\", \"-c\", cmdStr)\n    31→\tcmd.Dir = workDir\n    32→\n    33→\t// Pass run context env vars so script steps can use \"cloche get/set\"\n    34→\tif a.RunID != \"\" {\n    35→\t\tcmd.Env = append(os.Environ(),\n    36→\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID=\"+a.RunID,\n    37→\t\t\t\"CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR=\"+workDir,\n    38→\t\t)\n    39→\t}\n    40→\n    41→\tvar output []byte\n    42→\tvar err error\n    43→\n    44→\tif a.StatusWriter != nil {\n    45→\t\toutput, err = a.executeStreaming(cmd, step.Name)\n    46→\t} else {\n    47→\t\toutput, err = cmd.CombinedOutput()\n    48→\t}\n    49→\n    50→\t// Extract result marker before writing logs\n    51→\tmarkerResult, cleanOutput, found := protocol.ExtractResult(output)\n    52→\n    53→\t// Write cleaned output to log file\n    54→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"output\")\n    55→\tif mkErr := os.MkdirAll(outputDir, 0755); mkErr == nil {\n    56→\t\t_ = os.WriteFile(filepath.Join(outputDir, step.Name+\".log\"), cleanOutput, 0644)\n    57→\t}\n    58→\n    59→\tisAgent := step.Type == domain.StepTypeAgent\n    60→\n    61→\tif err != nil {\n    62→\t\tif _, ok := err.(*exec.ExitError); ok {\n    63→\t\t\tresult := \"fail\"\n    64→\t\t\tif found {\n    65→\t\t\t\tresult = markerResult\n    66→\t\t\t}\n    67→\t\t\tprotocol.AppendHistory(workDir, step.Name, result, isAgent, cleanOutput)\n    68→\t\t\treturn result, nil\n    69→\t\t}\n    70→\t\treturn \"\", err\n    71→\t}\n    72→\n    73→\tresult := \"success\"\n    74→\tif found {\n    75→\t\tresult = markerResult\n    76→\t}\n    77→\tprotocol.AppendHistory(workDir, step.Name, result, isAgent, cleanOutput)\n    78→\treturn result, nil\n    79→}\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BzjcVAg47gGUAAG5dSfXCB","session_id":"46588779-0c89-4fa7-bd14-27979381b9bd","uuid":"5a1daf2f-fd06-4609-b653-a027b339d1f5"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a190c07620e78791e","tool_use_id":"toolu_01BzjcVAg47gGUAAG5dSfXCB","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore codebase structure","usage":{"total_tokens":75590,"tool_uses":47,"duration_ms":150414},"uuid":"ec48da8e-4525-483b-a8d2-48f8f997d4e9","session_id":"46588779-0c89-4fa7-bd14-27979381b9bd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BzjcVAg47gGUAAG5dSfXCB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive knowledge of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's a detailed breakdown of the architecture, key types, and execution flows:\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Three Binaries (Single Go Module)**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/` - CLI client (short-lived)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/` - Daemon (long-running)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/` - In-container agent (autonomous)\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture**\n- Domain logic in `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n- Ports (interfaces) in `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n- Adapters in `/workspace/internal/adapters/`\n\n---\n\n### 1. Domain Types and Run State Machine\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\n#### Run Structure\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState  // pending → running → succeeded/failed/cancelled\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string  // Git HEAD at run start for result branch creation\n    ContainerKept  bool\n    Title          string\n    IsHost         bool    // true for host workflow runs vs container runs\n    ParentRunID    string  // ID of parent host run for child container runs\n    TaskID         string  // optional task ID from daemon loop\n}\n```\n\n#### RunState Transitions\n- **RunStatePending** → **RunStateRunning** → **RunStateSucceeded/RunStateFailed/RunStateCancelled**\n- Methods: `Start()`, `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n- Helper: `TaskAggregateStatus()` computes aggregate status for task attempts (prefers host runs)\n\n#### StepExecution (Captures)\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string  // \"success\", \"fail\", error marker\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string\n}\n```\n\n#### Workflow Structure\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire            // direct edges: (step, result) → next_steps\n    Collects  []Collect         // conditional aggregators\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string // workflow-level config (e.g. \"container.image\")\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType  // \"agent\", \"script\", \"workflow\"\n    Results []string  // possible result values\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n#### Run ID Generation\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/domain/namegen.go`\n```\nFormat: <workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>-<hex>\nExample: develop-vivid-bear-040e\n```\n\n#### Output Path Evaluation (for output mappings)\n```go\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment  // SegmentField or SegmentIndex\n}\n\n// Supports JSON navigation: .field[0].nested\nfunc (p OutputPath) Evaluate(raw []byte) (string, error)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Ports (Interfaces)\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\n#### RunStore Interface\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsFiltered(ctx context.Context, filter domain.RunListFilter) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### ContainerRuntime Interface\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {  // optional\n    EnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n#### AgentAdapter Interface\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n#### CaptureStore Interface (for step execution history)\n```go\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### LogStore Interface\n```go\ntype LogFileEntry struct {\n    ID        int64\n    RunID     string\n    StepName  string\n    FileType  string  // \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    FilePath  string\n    FileSize  int64\n    CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx context.Context, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx context.Context, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx context.Context, runID, fileType string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. SQLite Adapter\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n- **Database**: `~/.config/cloche/cloche.db`\n- **Mode**: WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) for concurrent access\n- **Connection**: Single serialized connection to prevent SQLite locking issues\n- **Tables**:\n  - `runs` - Run metadata (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, timestamps, container_id, etc.)\n  - `step_executions` - Step execution history with captures\n  - `log_files` - Extracted log file indexes\n\n---\n\n### 4. Docker Adapter\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`, `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go`\n\n#### Container Lifecycle\n1. **Create** with:\n   - Workdir: `/workspace`\n   - User: root (then chowned to agent)\n   - Env vars: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, extra mounts\n   - CMD: `cloche-agent <workflow-path>` with chown + su agent wrapper\n   - Network: full access (not isolated)\n\n2. **Start** (actually run with `docker start`)\n\n3. **AttachOutput** (read JSON-lines status messages from stdout)\n\n4. **Extract Results** (via `docker cp /workspace/.cloche/output/* → project/.cloche/<runid>/output/`)\n\n5. **Logs** (capture container stdout/stderr to container.log)\n\n6. **Remove** (when not --keep-container and run succeeded)\n\n#### Result Extraction\n- Extracts step output files and creates git branches\n- Branch naming: `cloche/<run-id>` based on workflow-level base SHA\n- Result state determines branch: succeeded, failed, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Agent Adapters\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/`\n\n#### Generic Adapter (`generic.go`)\n- Executes script steps: `sh -c <run config>`\n- Checks for result marker in output\n- Sets env: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`\n- Can stream output via StatusWriter\n\n#### Prompt Adapter (`prompt/prompt.go`)\n- Executes agent prompt steps\n- Command fallback chain: claude, custom agents\n- Assembles prompt from:\n  - Step's `prompt` config\n  - Previous step output (wired in)\n  - From `.cloche/prompt.txt` or `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n- Default args for known agents (e.g., claude: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose`)\n- Attempt counting: `max_attempts` config prevents infinite retry loops\n- Result extraction: looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT=<marker>` in output\n\n---\n\n### 6. Engine (Step Executor)\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n#### Core Engine Algorithm\n```go\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor\n    status         StatusHandler\n    maxSteps       int  // default 1000\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration  // default 30 min\n}\n\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n#### Execution Flow\n1. **Validate** workflow (entry exists, all results wired, no orphans)\n2. **Launch entry step** in goroutine\n3. **Main loop** (select on results channel):\n   - Wait for step completion\n   - Record result in run\n   - Resolve **wiring**: `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)` → list of target steps\n   - Launch all targets (fanout support)\n   - Check **collects**: conditional gates that aggregate results from multiple steps\n   - Continue until active count reaches 0\n4. **Terminal states**: \"done\" or \"abort\" targets increment counters\n5. **Failure modes**:\n   - Undeclared result → fail\n   - No wiring and no collect → fail\n   - Exceeds max steps → fail\n   - Context cancelled → cancelled\n\n#### Status Handler\n```go\ntype StatusHandler interface {\n    OnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    OnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n}\n```\n\nReceives notifications for all step transitions, persists to store and log broadcaster.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Container-Side Agent\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n\n#### Runner (`internal/agent/runner.go`)\n```go\ntype RunnerConfig struct {\n    WorkflowPath string\n    WorkDir      string\n    StatusOutput io.Writer  // where to write JSON-lines status\n    RunID        string\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n#### Execution Pipeline\n1. **Parse** `.cloche/<workflow-name>.cloche` from WorkflowPath\n2. **Load adapters**:\n   - Generic (for script steps)\n   - Prompt (for agent steps with prompt config)\n3. **Create engine** with stepExecutor\n4. **Create logstream writer** (unified log to full.log)\n5. **Run engine** with wf\n6. **Stream status** as JSON-lines:\n   - `step_started: <step>`\n   - `step_completed: <step> → <result>`\n   - `run_completed: <final-state>`\n   - `error: <message>`\n\n#### Step Executor (Container Side)\n- **Script steps**: Run generic adapter, log output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n- **Agent steps with `run`**: Run generic adapter\n- **Agent steps with `prompt`**: Run prompt adapter, copy to llm-<step>.log\n\n#### Per-Run Attempt Counting\n- File: `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>`\n- Reset on success\n- Incremented per attempt\n\n---\n\n### 8. Host Executor\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n#### Executor Structure\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string  // main branch worktree; scripts execute here\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string  // step output directory\n    Wires         []domain.Wire\n    HostRunID     string  // parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n}\n```\n\n#### Step Execution (Host Side)\n1. **Script steps** (domain.StepTypeScript):\n   - `sh -c <run config>` in scriptDir()\n   - Env: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`\n   - Output mappings resolved from wires\n   - Result extraction: looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT=<marker>`\n\n2. **Workflow steps** (domain.StepTypeWorkflow):\n   - Dispatch via Dispatcher.RunWorkflow() → creates child container run\n   - Link child: `childRun.ParentRunID = HostRunID`, `TaskID` propagated\n   - Poll `Store.GetRun()` every 2 sec until terminal state\n   - Maps: succeeded → \"success\", failed/cancelled → \"fail\"\n   - Child run ID written to step output\n\n3. **Agent steps** (domain.StepTypeAgent):\n   - Use prompt adapter on host\n   - Prompt from previous step or `prompt_step` config\n   - Write to `.cloche/<host-run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Copy adapter output to executor's output path\n\n#### Output Management\n- **Output directory**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n- **Step output file**: `<output-dir>/<step-name>.out`\n- **Output mapping resolution**: Walks wires to find source step, reads output, evaluates path, returns mapped env vars\n\n#### Main Worktree Detection\n```go\nfunc MainWorktreeDir(projectDir string) string\n```\nUses `git worktree list --porcelain` to find main worktree (executes scripts from there).\n\n---\n\n### 9. Host Runner and Loop\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n#### Host Runner\n```go\ntype Runner struct {\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    Captures      ports.CaptureStore\n    LogBroadcast  *logstream.Broadcaster\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n    SkipRunRecord bool\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runner) RunNamed(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*RunResult, error)\nfunc (r *Runner) RunNamedWithID(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, runID string) (*RunResult, error)\n```\n\n#### Execution\n1. **Find host workflow** in any `.cloche/*.cloche` file\n2. **Create output directory**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n3. **Persist host run**: Mark `IsHost = true`\n4. **Create executor** with wiring from workflow\n5. **Run engine** with executor\n6. **Status handler** (`hostStatusHandler`) saves captures and broadcasts logs like container side\n7. **Finalize**: Persist final run state\n\n#### Host Loop (Orchestration)\n```go\ntype Loop struct {\n    config     LoopConfig\n    listTasks  ListTasksFunc\n    mainFn     MainFunc\n    finalizeFn FinalizeFunc\n    runner     RunFunc  // legacy\n    store      ports.RunStore\n    // State\n    mu        sync.Mutex\n    running   bool\n    taskRuns  map[string]TaskAssignment\n    dedup     map[string]time.Time  // suppress reassignment within DedupTimeout\n}\n\nfunc NewPhaseLoop(cfg LoopConfig, store, listTasksFn, mainFn, finalizeFn) *Loop\n```\n\n#### Three-Phase Orchestration\n1. **List-tasks phase**: Discover available tasks (runs list-tasks workflow)\n2. **Main phase**: Run main workflow for each open task (up to MaxConcurrent)\n3. **Finalize phase**: Run finalize workflow with main result (success/fail)\n4. **Dedup**: Suppress reassignment of same task ID within DedupTimeout\n5. **Halt on error**: If StopOnError = true, halt loop but let in-flight work complete\n\n---\n\n### 10. gRPC Service and Daemon\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n#### RPC Methods\n```proto\nservice ClocheService {\n    rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) returns (RunWorkflowResponse);\n    rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) returns (GetStatusResponse);\n    rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);\n    rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse);\n    rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse);\n    rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) returns (ShutdownResponse);\n    rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse);\n    rpc EnableLoop(EnableLoopRequest) returns (EnableLoopResponse);\n    rpc DisableLoop(DisableLoopRequest) returns (DisableLoopResponse);\n    rpc ResumeLoop(ResumeLoopRequest) returns (ResumeLoopResponse);\n    rpc GetProjectInfo(GetProjectInfoRequest) returns (GetProjectInfoResponse);\n    rpc GetVersion(GetVersionRequest) returns (GetVersionResponse);\n}\n```\n\n#### gRPC Server Implementation\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n```go\ntype ClocheServer struct {\n    store        ports.RunStore\n    captures     ports.CaptureStore\n    logStore     ports.LogStore\n    container    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    defaultImage string\n    evolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    logBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    mu           sync.Mutex\n    runIDs       map[string]string  // run_id → container_id\n    loops        map[string]*host.Loop\n}\n```\n\n#### RunWorkflow Flow\n1. **Detect workflow location**:\n   - If host workflow → `runHostWorkflow()` → spawn host runner goroutine\n   - Else → container workflow → launch container\n\n2. **Container workflow** (launchAndTrack):\n   - Auto-rebuild image if Dockerfile changed (ImageEnsurer)\n   - Generate run ID with collision avoidance\n   - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Create Run record in store (state=pending)\n   - Launch container in background (launchAndTrack goroutine)\n   - Return RunWorkflowResponse immediately\n\n3. **trackRun** (background goroutine):\n   - AttachOutput and parse JSON-lines status messages\n   - Update run state with step starts/completions\n   - Save captures to CaptureStore\n   - Broadcast logs if logBroadcaster configured\n   - Wait for container exit\n   - Extract step output files (CopyFrom)\n   - Extract results to git branch via docker.ExtractResults()\n   - Finalize run state based on agent result or exit code\n   - Fire evolution trigger\n   - Container retention policy: keep on failure or --keep-container\n   - Remove from tracking map\n\n#### Host Workflow Flow\n1. Create Runner with Dispatcher=server (for dispatch callbacks)\n2. Spawn background goroutine to run host workflow\n3. Return RunWorkflowResponse with run ID immediately\n4. Host runner persists host run as IsHost=true\n5. Can dispatch child container runs via Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()\n\n#### Log Streaming\n```\nStreamLogs(runID, stepName, logType, follow, limit)\n→ reads from logstore or live broadcasts\n→ supports tail -f style (follow) and line limit\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. CLI Commands\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n#### Command Structure\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--issue ID] [--keep-container]\ncloche status <run-id>\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type full|script|llm] [--follow] [--lines N]\ncloche list [--all] [--project <dir>] [--state pending|running|succeeded|failed] [--limit N]\ncloche stop <run-id>\ncloche delete <container-id>\ncloche loop {enable|disable|resume} [--project <dir>] [--max-concurrent N]\ncloche project info [--project <dir>]\ncloche workflow [<name>]\ncloche validate [--project <dir>]\ncloche get <key>\ncloche set <key> <value>\ncloche health\ncloche -v / --version\n```\n\n#### Connection Model\n- Commands connect to daemon via gRPC at `CLOCHE_ADDR` (default: `unix:///home/<user>/.config/cloche/cloche.sock`)\n- Short timeout (30s) for gRPC calls\n- Commands that don't need daemon: init, health, get, set, tasks, workflow, project, validate\n\n---\n\n### 12. Protocol and Status Messages\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`, `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go`\n\n#### Status Message Types (JSON-lines from agent)\n```go\ntype MessageType string\nconst (\n    MsgStepStarted   = \"step_started\"   // StepName set\n    MsgStepCompleted = \"step_completed\" // StepName + Result set\n    MsgRunCompleted  = \"run_completed\"  // Result set (final state)\n    MsgRunTitle      = \"run_title\"      // Message set (one-line summary)\n    MsgLog           = \"log\"            // Message set (live streaming content)\n    MsgError         = \"error\"          // StepName + Message set\n)\n```\n\n#### Result Marker Extraction\n- Looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT=<marker>` or output marker comment\n- Extracts from step output before logging\n- Maps to declared results in step\n\n#### History Tracking\n- File: `.cloche/history.json`\n- Per-step success/failure with attempt count\n- Used by prompt adapter for context\n\n---\n\n### 13. Workflow DSL\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`\n\n#### Parse Functions\n```go\nParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)  // single workflow\nParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)       // single host workflow\nParseAll(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)  // multiple workflows, auto-detect location\nParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)  // multiple in host.cloche\n```\n\n#### Syntax Elements\n- **Workflow**: `workflow <name> { ... }`\n- **Host block**: `host { }` marks workflow as LocationHost\n- **Steps**: `step <name> { type: ..., ... }`\n- **Step types**: agent, script, workflow\n- **Wiring**: `<step> <result> → <next-step>`\n- **Collect**: aggregator with mode all|any\n- **Config**: workflow-level and step-level key-value pairs\n\n---\n\n### 14. Key File Paths\n\n**Project Structure**\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche           # container workflow definition\n│   ├── host.cloche              # host workflow definitions with host { } blocks\n│   ├── Dockerfile\n│   ├── prompts/                 # prompt templates\n│   ├── scripts/                 # host-side helper scripts\n│   ├── overrides/               # files copied into container /workspace\n│   └── <run-id>/\n│       ├── prompt.txt           # prompt for this run\n│       ├── output/              # extracted step output files\n│       │   ├── <step>.out\n│       │   ├── llm-<step>.log\n│       │   └── container.log\n│       └── full.log             # unified log (host runs only)\n├── src/                         # project source (untouched by cloche)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n**Daemon Config**\n- Global: `~/.config/cloche/config` (YAML)\n- Per-project: `.cloche/config.yaml`\n- DB: `~/.config/cloche/cloche.db` (SQLite)\n- Socket: `unix:///home/<user>/.config/cloche/cloche.sock`\n\n---\n\n### 15. Run Lifecycle Summary\n\n#### Container Run\n1. **Pending**: Created in store, container start initiated\n2. **Running**: Container started, tracking status messages\n3. **Succeeded/Failed**: Container exited, results extracted to git branch, container optionally kept\n4. **Cancelled**: Stop RPC or context cancellation\n\n#### Host Run\n1. **Pending**: Created in store\n2. **Running**: Steps executing, dispatching child container runs\n3. **Succeeded/Failed**: All steps complete\n4. **Cancelled**: Loop halted or context cancelled\n\n#### Task Association\n- `Run.TaskID` links run to a task from list-tasks\n- Host runner and loop propagate TaskID to child runs\n- Used for three-phase orchestration (list-tasks → main → finalize)\n\n---\n\n### 16. Key Interfaces and Data Flow\n\n**Request → Response Flow for `cloche run`**\n```\nCLI (cloche run --workflow develop)\n  → gRPC client.RunWorkflow()\n  → cloched ClocheServer.RunWorkflow()\n  → detect location (container vs host)\n  → create Run(pending), write prompt, return RunID immediately\n  → background: launchAndTrack() or hostRunner.Run()\n    → loop: trackRun() monitors status messages\n    → updates Run state, step executions, broadcasts logs\n    → extracts results, finalizes\n```\n\n**Log Retrieval Flow**\n```\nCLI (cloche logs <run-id>)\n  → gRPC client.StreamLogs()\n  → cloched ClocheServer.StreamLogs()\n  → reads logstore or pulls from live broadcaster\n  → streams LogEntry messages back to CLI\n  → CLI writes to stdout\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive map covers all major components, types, interfaces, and execution flows. You now have the detailed knowledge needed to extend, debug, or integrate with Cloche."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a190c07620e78791e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 82078\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 150419</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46588779-0c89-4fa7-bd14-27979381b9bd","uuid":"892bf01a-6e7d-4eb4-b9e6-1a98d2a37dd7","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. How existing CLI commands are structured (look at cmd/cloche/ for patterns)\n2. The domain types - Run, Step, Result, Workflow (in internal/domain/)\n3. The ports/interfaces - RunStore, AgentAdapter, ContainerRuntime (in internal/ports/)\n4. How the agent executes workflows (cmd/cloche-agent/ and related code)\n5. How the host executor works (internal/host/)\n6. The gRPC service definitions (look for .proto files)\n7. How existing commands like `run`, `stop`, `status` are implemented\n8. The adapters - especially Docker, Claude Code agent adapters\n\nGive me detailed file paths, key types, interfaces, and function signatures. I need to understand:\n- How a run is created and tracked\n- How steps are executed\n- How the agent walks the workflow graph\n- The gRPC API between CLI and daemon\n- How containers are managed\n- Run states and transitions\n- How prompt steps vs script steps are executed differently\n","agentId":"a190c07620e78791e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive knowledge of the codebase. Let me create a detailed summary document.\n\n## Comprehensive Cloche Codebase Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's a detailed breakdown of the architecture, key types, and execution flows:\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Three Binaries (Single Go Module)**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/` - CLI client (short-lived)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/` - Daemon (long-running)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/` - In-container agent (autonomous)\n\n**Hexagonal Architecture**\n- Domain logic in `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n- Ports (interfaces) in `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n- Adapters in `/workspace/internal/adapters/`\n\n---\n\n### 1. Domain Types and Run State Machine\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`, `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`\n\n#### Run Structure\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n    ID             string\n    WorkflowName   string\n    State          RunState  // pending → running → succeeded/failed/cancelled\n    ActiveSteps    []string\n    StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n    StartedAt      time.Time\n    CompletedAt    time.Time\n    ProjectDir     string\n    ErrorMessage   string\n    ContainerID    string\n    BaseSHA        string  // Git HEAD at run start for result branch creation\n    ContainerKept  bool\n    Title          string\n    IsHost         bool    // true for host workflow runs vs container runs\n    ParentRunID    string  // ID of parent host run for child container runs\n    TaskID         string  // optional task ID from daemon loop\n}\n```\n\n#### RunState Transitions\n- **RunStatePending** → **RunStateRunning** → **RunStateSucceeded/RunStateFailed/RunStateCancelled**\n- Methods: `Start()`, `RecordStepStart()`, `RecordStepComplete()`, `Complete()`, `Fail()`\n- Helper: `TaskAggregateStatus()` computes aggregate status for task attempts (prefers host runs)\n\n#### StepExecution (Captures)\n```go\ntype StepExecution struct {\n    StepName    string\n    Result      string  // \"success\", \"fail\", error marker\n    StartedAt   time.Time\n    CompletedAt time.Time\n    Logs        string\n    GitRef      string\n}\n```\n\n#### Workflow Structure\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n    Name      string\n    Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n    Steps     map[string]*Step\n    Wiring    []Wire            // direct edges: (step, result) → next_steps\n    Collects  []Collect         // conditional aggregators\n    EntryStep string\n    Config    map[string]string // workflow-level config (e.g. \"container.image\")\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n    Name    string\n    Type    StepType  // \"agent\", \"script\", \"workflow\"\n    Results []string  // possible result values\n    Config  map[string]string\n}\n```\n\n#### Run ID Generation\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/domain/namegen.go`\n```\nFormat: <workflow>-<adjective>-<noun>-<hex>\nExample: develop-vivid-bear-040e\n```\n\n#### Output Path Evaluation (for output mappings)\n```go\ntype OutputPath struct {\n    Segments []PathSegment  // SegmentField or SegmentIndex\n}\n\n// Supports JSON navigation: .field[0].nested\nfunc (p OutputPath) Evaluate(raw []byte) (string, error)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Ports (Interfaces)\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\n#### RunStore Interface\n```go\ntype RunStore interface {\n    CreateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    GetRun(ctx context.Context, id string) (*domain.Run, error)\n    UpdateRun(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) error\n    DeleteRun(ctx context.Context, id string) error\n    ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListRunsFiltered(ctx context.Context, filter domain.RunListFilter) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n    ListProjects(ctx context.Context) ([]string, error)\n    ListChildRuns(ctx context.Context, parentRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### ContainerRuntime Interface\n```go\ntype ContainerRuntime interface {\n    Start(ctx context.Context, cfg ContainerConfig) (containerID string, err error)\n    Stop(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    AttachOutput(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n    Wait(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (exitCode int, err error)\n    CopyFrom(ctx context.Context, containerID string, srcPath, dstPath string) error\n    Logs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    Remove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    Inspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype ImageEnsurer interface {  // optional\n    EnsureImage(ctx context.Context, projectDir, image string) error\n}\n```\n\n#### AgentAdapter Interface\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n#### CaptureStore Interface (for step execution history)\n```go\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n#### LogStore Interface\n```go\ntype LogFileEntry struct {\n    ID        int64\n    RunID     string\n    StepName  string\n    FileType  string  // \"full\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n    FilePath  string\n    FileSize  int64\n    CreatedAt time.Time\n}\n\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx context.Context, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx context.Context, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx context.Context, runID, fileType string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. SQLite Adapter\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n- **Database**: `~/.config/cloche/cloche.db`\n- **Mode**: WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) for concurrent access\n- **Connection**: Single serialized connection to prevent SQLite locking issues\n- **Tables**:\n  - `runs` - Run metadata (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, timestamps, container_id, etc.)\n  - `step_executions` - Step execution history with captures\n  - `log_files` - Extracted log file indexes\n\n---\n\n### 4. Docker Adapter\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`, `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/extract.go`\n\n#### Container Lifecycle\n1. **Create** with:\n   - Workdir: `/workspace`\n   - User: root (then chowned to agent)\n   - Env vars: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, extra mounts\n   - CMD: `cloche-agent <workflow-path>` with chown + su agent wrapper\n   - Network: full access (not isolated)\n\n2. **Start** (actually run with `docker start`)\n\n3. **AttachOutput** (read JSON-lines status messages from stdout)\n\n4. **Extract Results** (via `docker cp /workspace/.cloche/output/* → project/.cloche/<runid>/output/`)\n\n5. **Logs** (capture container stdout/stderr to container.log)\n\n6. **Remove** (when not --keep-container and run succeeded)\n\n#### Result Extraction\n- Extracts step output files and creates git branches\n- Branch naming: `cloche/<run-id>` based on workflow-level base SHA\n- Result state determines branch: succeeded, failed, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Agent Adapters\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/`\n\n#### Generic Adapter (`generic.go`)\n- Executes script steps: `sh -c <run config>`\n- Checks for result marker in output\n- Sets env: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`\n- Can stream output via StatusWriter\n\n#### Prompt Adapter (`prompt/prompt.go`)\n- Executes agent prompt steps\n- Command fallback chain: claude, custom agents\n- Assembles prompt from:\n  - Step's `prompt` config\n  - Previous step output (wired in)\n  - From `.cloche/prompt.txt` or `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n- Default args for known agents (e.g., claude: `-p --output-format stream-json --verbose`)\n- Attempt counting: `max_attempts` config prevents infinite retry loops\n- Result extraction: looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT=<marker>` in output\n\n---\n\n### 6. Engine (Step Executor)\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\n#### Core Engine Algorithm\n```go\ntype StepExecutor interface {\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step) (string, error)\n}\n\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor\n    status         StatusHandler\n    maxSteps       int  // default 1000\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration  // default 30 min\n}\n\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n#### Execution Flow\n1. **Validate** workflow (entry exists, all results wired, no orphans)\n2. **Launch entry step** in goroutine\n3. **Main loop** (select on results channel):\n   - Wait for step completion\n   - Record result in run\n   - Resolve **wiring**: `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)` → list of target steps\n   - Launch all targets (fanout support)\n   - Check **collects**: conditional gates that aggregate results from multiple steps\n   - Continue until active count reaches 0\n4. **Terminal states**: \"done\" or \"abort\" targets increment counters\n5. **Failure modes**:\n   - Undeclared result → fail\n   - No wiring and no collect → fail\n   - Exceeds max steps → fail\n   - Context cancelled → cancelled\n\n#### Status Handler\n```go\ntype StatusHandler interface {\n    OnStepStart(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step)\n    OnStepComplete(run *domain.Run, step *domain.Step, result string)\n    OnRunComplete(run *domain.Run)\n}\n```\n\nReceives notifications for all step transitions, persists to store and log broadcaster.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Container-Side Agent\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`\n\n#### Runner (`internal/agent/runner.go`)\n```go\ntype RunnerConfig struct {\n    WorkflowPath string\n    WorkDir      string\n    StatusOutput io.Writer  // where to write JSON-lines status\n    RunID        string\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n#### Execution Pipeline\n1. **Parse** `.cloche/<workflow-name>.cloche` from WorkflowPath\n2. **Load adapters**:\n   - Generic (for script steps)\n   - Prompt (for agent steps with prompt config)\n3. **Create engine** with stepExecutor\n4. **Create logstream writer** (unified log to full.log)\n5. **Run engine** with wf\n6. **Stream status** as JSON-lines:\n   - `step_started: <step>`\n   - `step_completed: <step> → <result>`\n   - `run_completed: <final-state>`\n   - `error: <message>`\n\n#### Step Executor (Container Side)\n- **Script steps**: Run generic adapter, log output to `.cloche/output/<step>.log`\n- **Agent steps with `run`**: Run generic adapter\n- **Agent steps with `prompt`**: Run prompt adapter, copy to llm-<step>.log\n\n#### Per-Run Attempt Counting\n- File: `.cloche/attempt_count/<step-name>`\n- Reset on success\n- Incremented per attempt\n\n---\n\n### 8. Host Executor\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n#### Executor Structure\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string  // main branch worktree; scripts execute here\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string  // step output directory\n    Wires         []domain.Wire\n    HostRunID     string  // parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n}\n```\n\n#### Step Execution (Host Side)\n1. **Script steps** (domain.StepTypeScript):\n   - `sh -c <run config>` in scriptDir()\n   - Env: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`\n   - Output mappings resolved from wires\n   - Result extraction: looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT=<marker>`\n\n2. **Workflow steps** (domain.StepTypeWorkflow):\n   - Dispatch via Dispatcher.RunWorkflow() → creates child container run\n   - Link child: `childRun.ParentRunID = HostRunID`, `TaskID` propagated\n   - Poll `Store.GetRun()` every 2 sec until terminal state\n   - Maps: succeeded → \"success\", failed/cancelled → \"fail\"\n   - Child run ID written to step output\n\n3. **Agent steps** (domain.StepTypeAgent):\n   - Use prompt adapter on host\n   - Prompt from previous step or `prompt_step` config\n   - Write to `.cloche/<host-run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Copy adapter output to executor's output path\n\n#### Output Management\n- **Output directory**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n- **Step output file**: `<output-dir>/<step-name>.out`\n- **Output mapping resolution**: Walks wires to find source step, reads output, evaluates path, returns mapped env vars\n\n#### Main Worktree Detection\n```go\nfunc MainWorktreeDir(projectDir string) string\n```\nUses `git worktree list --porcelain` to find main worktree (executes scripts from there).\n\n---\n\n### 9. Host Runner and Loop\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n#### Host Runner\n```go\ntype Runner struct {\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    Captures      ports.CaptureStore\n    LogBroadcast  *logstream.Broadcaster\n    TaskID        string\n    ExtraEnv      []string\n    SkipRunRecord bool\n}\n\nfunc (r *Runner) RunNamed(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*RunResult, error)\nfunc (r *Runner) RunNamedWithID(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, runID string) (*RunResult, error)\n```\n\n#### Execution\n1. **Find host workflow** in any `.cloche/*.cloche` file\n2. **Create output directory**: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n3. **Persist host run**: Mark `IsHost = true`\n4. **Create executor** with wiring from workflow\n5. **Run engine** with executor\n6. **Status handler** (`hostStatusHandler`) saves captures and broadcasts logs like container side\n7. **Finalize**: Persist final run state\n\n#### Host Loop (Orchestration)\n```go\ntype Loop struct {\n    config     LoopConfig\n    listTasks  ListTasksFunc\n    mainFn     MainFunc\n    finalizeFn FinalizeFunc\n    runner     RunFunc  // legacy\n    store      ports.RunStore\n    // State\n    mu        sync.Mutex\n    running   bool\n    taskRuns  map[string]TaskAssignment\n    dedup     map[string]time.Time  // suppress reassignment within DedupTimeout\n}\n\nfunc NewPhaseLoop(cfg LoopConfig, store, listTasksFn, mainFn, finalizeFn) *Loop\n```\n\n#### Three-Phase Orchestration\n1. **List-tasks phase**: Discover available tasks (runs list-tasks workflow)\n2. **Main phase**: Run main workflow for each open task (up to MaxConcurrent)\n3. **Finalize phase**: Run finalize workflow with main result (success/fail)\n4. **Dedup**: Suppress reassignment of same task ID within DedupTimeout\n5. **Halt on error**: If StopOnError = true, halt loop but let in-flight work complete\n\n---\n\n### 10. gRPC Service and Daemon\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n#### RPC Methods\n```proto\nservice ClocheService {\n    rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) returns (RunWorkflowResponse);\n    rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) returns (GetStatusResponse);\n    rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry);\n    rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse);\n    rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse);\n    rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) returns (ShutdownResponse);\n    rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse);\n    rpc EnableLoop(EnableLoopRequest) returns (EnableLoopResponse);\n    rpc DisableLoop(DisableLoopRequest) returns (DisableLoopResponse);\n    rpc ResumeLoop(ResumeLoopRequest) returns (ResumeLoopResponse);\n    rpc GetProjectInfo(GetProjectInfoRequest) returns (GetProjectInfoResponse);\n    rpc GetVersion(GetVersionRequest) returns (GetVersionResponse);\n}\n```\n\n#### gRPC Server Implementation\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n```go\ntype ClocheServer struct {\n    store        ports.RunStore\n    captures     ports.CaptureStore\n    logStore     ports.LogStore\n    container    ports.ContainerRuntime\n    defaultImage string\n    evolution    *evolution.Trigger\n    logBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    mu           sync.Mutex\n    runIDs       map[string]string  // run_id → container_id\n    loops        map[string]*host.Loop\n}\n```\n\n#### RunWorkflow Flow\n1. **Detect workflow location**:\n   - If host workflow → `runHostWorkflow()` → spawn host runner goroutine\n   - Else → container workflow → launch container\n\n2. **Container workflow** (launchAndTrack):\n   - Auto-rebuild image if Dockerfile changed (ImageEnsurer)\n   - Generate run ID with collision avoidance\n   - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Create Run record in store (state=pending)\n   - Launch container in background (launchAndTrack goroutine)\n   - Return RunWorkflowResponse immediately\n\n3. **trackRun** (background goroutine):\n   - AttachOutput and parse JSON-lines status messages\n   - Update run state with step starts/completions\n   - Save captures to CaptureStore\n   - Broadcast logs if logBroadcaster configured\n   - Wait for container exit\n   - Extract step output files (CopyFrom)\n   - Extract results to git branch via docker.ExtractResults()\n   - Finalize run state based on agent result or exit code\n   - Fire evolution trigger\n   - Container retention policy: keep on failure or --keep-container\n   - Remove from tracking map\n\n#### Host Workflow Flow\n1. Create Runner with Dispatcher=server (for dispatch callbacks)\n2. Spawn background goroutine to run host workflow\n3. Return RunWorkflowResponse with run ID immediately\n4. Host runner persists host run as IsHost=true\n5. Can dispatch child container runs via Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()\n\n#### Log Streaming\n```\nStreamLogs(runID, stepName, logType, follow, limit)\n→ reads from logstore or live broadcasts\n→ supports tail -f style (follow) and line limit\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. CLI Commands\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n#### Command Structure\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--issue ID] [--keep-container]\ncloche status <run-id>\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type full|script|llm] [--follow] [--lines N]\ncloche list [--all] [--project <dir>] [--state pending|running|succeeded|failed] [--limit N]\ncloche stop <run-id>\ncloche delete <container-id>\ncloche loop {enable|disable|resume} [--project <dir>] [--max-concurrent N]\ncloche project info [--project <dir>]\ncloche workflow [<name>]\ncloche validate [--project <dir>]\ncloche get <key>\ncloche set <key> <value>\ncloche health\ncloche -v / --version\n```\n\n#### Connection Model\n- Commands connect to daemon via gRPC at `CLOCHE_ADDR` (default: `unix:///home/<user>/.config/cloche/cloche.sock`)\n- Short timeout (30s) for gRPC calls\n- Commands that don't need daemon: init, health, get, set, tasks, workflow, project, validate\n\n---\n\n### 12. Protocol and Status Messages\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`, `/workspace/internal/protocol/result.go`\n\n#### Status Message Types (JSON-lines from agent)\n```go\ntype MessageType string\nconst (\n    MsgStepStarted   = \"step_started\"   // StepName set\n    MsgStepCompleted = \"step_completed\" // StepName + Result set\n    MsgRunCompleted  = \"run_completed\"  // Result set (final state)\n    MsgRunTitle      = \"run_title\"      // Message set (one-line summary)\n    MsgLog           = \"log\"            // Message set (live streaming content)\n    MsgError         = \"error\"          // StepName + Message set\n)\n```\n\n#### Result Marker Extraction\n- Looks for `CLOCHE_RESULT=<marker>` or output marker comment\n- Extracts from step output before logging\n- Maps to declared results in step\n\n#### History Tracking\n- File: `.cloche/history.json`\n- Per-step success/failure with attempt count\n- Used by prompt adapter for context\n\n---\n\n### 13. Workflow DSL\n\n**Location**: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`, `/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`\n\n#### Parse Functions\n```go\nParseForContainer(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)  // single workflow\nParseForHost(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)       // single host workflow\nParseAll(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)  // multiple workflows, auto-detect location\nParseAllForHost(input string) (map[string]*domain.Workflow, error)  // multiple in host.cloche\n```\n\n#### Syntax Elements\n- **Workflow**: `workflow <name> { ... }`\n- **Host block**: `host { }` marks workflow as LocationHost\n- **Steps**: `step <name> { type: ..., ... }`\n- **Step types**: agent, script, workflow\n- **Wiring**: `<step> <result> → <next-step>`\n- **Collect**: aggregator with mode all|any\n- **Config**: workflow-level and step-level key-value pairs\n\n---\n\n### 14. Key File Paths\n\n**Project Structure**\n```\nmy-project/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche           # container workflow definition\n│   ├── host.cloche              # host workflow definitions with host { } blocks\n│   ├── Dockerfile\n│   ├── prompts/                 # prompt templates\n│   ├── scripts/                 # host-side helper scripts\n│   ├── overrides/               # files copied into container /workspace\n│   └── <run-id>/\n│       ├── prompt.txt           # prompt for this run\n│       ├── output/              # extracted step output files\n│       │   ├── <step>.out\n│       │   ├── llm-<step>.log\n│       │   └── container.log\n│       └── full.log             # unified log (host runs only)\n├── src/                         # project source (untouched by cloche)\n└── CLAUDE.md\n```\n\n**Daemon Config**\n- Global: `~/.config/cloche/config` (YAML)\n- Per-project: `.cloche/config.yaml`\n- DB: `~/.config/cloche/cloche.db` (SQLite)\n- Socket: `unix:///home/<user>/.config/cloche/cloche.sock`\n\n---\n\n### 15. Run Lifecycle Summary\n\n#### Container Run\n1. **Pending**: Created in store, container start initiated\n2. **Running**: Container started, tracking status messages\n3. **Succeeded/Failed**: Container exited, results extracted to git branch, container optionally kept\n4. **Cancelled**: Stop RPC or context cancellation\n\n#### Host Run\n1. **Pending**: Created in store\n2. **Running**: Steps executing, dispatching child container runs\n3. **Succeeded/Failed**: All steps complete\n4. **Cancelled**: Loop halted or context cancelled\n\n#### Task Association\n- `Run.TaskID` links run to a task from list-tasks\n- Host runner and loop propagate TaskID to child runs\n- Used for three-phase orchestration (list-tasks → main → finalize)\n\n---\n\n### 16. Key Interfaces and Data Flow\n\n**Request → Response Flow for `cloche run`**\n```\nCLI (cloche run --workflow develop)\n  → gRPC client.RunWorkflow()\n  → cloched ClocheServer.RunWorkflow()\n  → detect location (container vs host)\n  → create Run(pending), write prompt, return RunID immediately\n  → background: launchAndTrack() or hostRunner.Run()\n    → loop: trackRun() monitors status messages\n    → updates Run state, step executions, broadcasts logs\n    → extracts results, finalizes\n```\n\n**Log Retrieval Flow**\n```\nCLI (cloche logs <run-id>)\n  → gRPC client.StreamLogs()\n  → cloched ClocheServer.StreamLogs()\n  → reads logstore or pulls from live broadcaster\n  → streams LogEntry messages back to CLI\n  → CLI writes to stdout\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive map covers all major components, types, interfaces, and execution flows. You now have the detailed knowledge needed to extend, debug, or integrate with Cloche."}],"totalDurationMs":150419,"totalTokens":82078,"totalToolUseCount":47,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1033,"cache_read_input_tokens":74308,"output_tokens":6737,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1033},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
